40|$|Traditional Intrusion Detection Systems (IDSs) mostly work off-line, {{without any}} direct runtime {{interaction}} or coordination with the applications (and with other IDSs) that they aim to protect. Including <b>intrusion</b> <b>detection</b> <b>and</b> <b>response</b> in the repertoire of an adaptive application extends its range of adaptivity and increases its chances for survival. In this paper we show how <b>intrusion</b> <b>detection</b> <b>and</b> <b>response</b> {{can be used}} to build agile, intrusion-aware applications under the Quality Objects (QuO) adaptive distributed middleware framework. 1...|$|E
